<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
For me, pets are expendable. I don't heal a pet *unless* it is the primary tank.<P>Example: My mage friend and I decide to kill Seafuries in OOT while waiting for the AC. He summons an earth pet to tank the beasts and I just do CH on the pet. We pretty much sit there and collect the loot, and the fights never get out of hand. (this was a long time ago, say in our early 50s)<P>In a group situation, the pet is nice to have as extra firepower, but the owner of the pet should know when to pull it back if it's taking too much of a beating. The others in the group are way too valuable and a cleric's mana is precious.<P>A pet doesn't have to do a CR.<P>In your situation, *maybe* I could see healing the pet, but not necessarily. Monks are pretty thin when it comes to hitpoints, as are mages and yourself. Sounds like you had a handful of work to do in your group, and it sounds like you did well. <BR>/ignore Angry_Mage_001<P>--------------------<P>Xiaojie<BR>Band-Aid<BR>High Priestess of the Blackened Heart<BR>Terris Thule
