<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
To Heal Pets or not?<P>I calculate the mana cost of summoning the pet versus the amount of mana taken to save it.<P>If saving the pet is the most efficient and doesn't endanger teammates by draining mana, then I will save the pet.<P>I also play a 47 Shaman and the mana cost of summoning a pet and buffing it are much higher than tossing it a superior heal. If there aren't a lot of pets with the same name in the zone, you can make a target key with the name of the pet on a social button.     i.e.   /target Gebeker<P>Gyrefal<P>PS: If the pet owner is clueless about keeping it under control and using it effectively, let the pet die and owner suck the mana loss. The owner will either wise up, or at the very least, stop visiting the Gebeker Menace on your team.<P>Gyrefal  49 Cleric Karana Server
</FONT>
