<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
In most group situations, I tell pet casters straight up that I do not use mana healing pets, if the subject is ever brought up.  As stated in an earlier post, the only time I would ever heal a pet is if it's serving as the primary tank.  A good example of that was tonight.  My best friend (a mage) and I were camping HG's in Rathe Mountains using his earth pet as the tank.  Otherwise, pets are completely expendable.  IMHO.<P>Don't get me wrong.  I love pets.  I think that, when controlled properly, pets add greatly to the potential, overall power of a group.  They do not, though, equal the importance of the lives of the players who make that group.  I don't think twice when a pet dies, and most pet casters I know don't either.  Some do seem to have an over exaggerated attatchment to their pets (and with mages I can atleast partially understand this feeling), but for the most part, people accept the fact that a pet is a "tool" to use in aiding the group, or caster (if solo), nothing more.
</FONT>
