<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sometimes I heal pets when the scenario calls for it...e.g. trying to kill Rak in the City of Mist for the shaman epic. <P>For those who don't know, Rak procs a 1500ish fire AE, so fighting him normally is all but impossible. The standard tactic is to have a couple (two minimum, 3 or 4 is better) of mages with buffed-up high-level fire pets standing by. A buffed-up tank pulls Rak, then the pets deal with him while the players stand back and heal the pets. They're pretty much immune to the AE, so it's just melee damage...takes a while, but it works.<P>Other times I heal pets are when the pet is being a main damage-taker...such as when you are small-grouping it with a mage or necro partner. <P>One example that comes to mind is when I did crystalline wurms in GD with a mage partner, his earth pet was our tank. He would send in the pet and Malise the wurm, making it more vulnerable to being rooted. Then it was just a matter of healing the pet while the mage nuked. Got a lot of spells that way, and the tactic applies just about anywhere.<P>But relative to a party member...pets are expendable. Never ever forget that. Healing a pet can be useful, but it's the players who matter. Nuff said.<P>--------------------<P>Galavant Greenlabel<BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=15436" TARGET=_blank>View my profile</A>
