It is not hard to heal a pet.<P>Most times I've seen it asked, it's something like "Heal Janober please"<P>All you have to do is type "/tar Jan" and you get the pet on target.<P>If you can't type that, make a hotkey for the pet to help you target faster.<P><BR>And since when did your mana become too good to be used on a lowly pet? Do you not heal paladins because they can heal themselves?<P><BR>How would you feel if your enchanter randomly cast pillage enchantment on a tank forcing you to rebuff? That's akin to what you're doing to the pet casters.<P><BR>I can understand if you're lom or busy doing other <I>pressing</I> tasks at the moment, and I can see a justifiable complaint if your magician refuses to do any healing of his own (same situation with druid), but I've yet to see any rational justification for a cleric to completely ignore the pet.<P>Arlina
