<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Enob:<P>I play a pet class and would say that you need to make a judgement as to whether a pet should/shouldn't be healed.  As a general rule of thumb, these are some things i would recommend you think about:<P>1. Is the pet critical to our group's survival at that moment in time?  If yes, heal pet.<P>2. Don't heal a pet at the expense/risk of another pc dying.  <P>3. Check your mana.  Are you lom?  If so, don't heal the pet.  I'd rather you save your mana for a heal on a pc and let my pet die.  <P>As a necro, i've only asked for pet heals when i thought it was critical to our group's survival (i've maybe asked for a dozen pet heals in 50+ lvls of necro play).  Some pet owners suffer from pet love (maybe they don't get enough RL love).  I think under the scenario you meantioned, you made the right decision.  You were LoM.  Save your mana just in case things get ugly.  Lets say you were 50% mana and things were under control/stabalizing, then mage may have had a point.  Either way, he shouldn't have given you a hard time about it.  Its only mana to him.  An Oom cleric potentially equals a dead party.<P>--------------------<P>The Man with the Plan
</FONT>
