ok i have a higher lvl mage as well as an upper lvl cleric. mages casting time is 12 secs or so on pets if you wait for mage to resummon and its dire straits thats a very long time...also their heal spell costs 100 mana if i remeber correctly..at 51 it heals an earth pet(51pet spell) about 5%. You really think thats mana efficient? no. If i group as a cleric with pet classes, i will usually throw a valor/reso line buff on the pet for good measure when i have the added mana. I will heal the pet if mana permits and party health isnt critical. Just a side note: for those of you who heal pets, do you notice a delay before you see the health bar move when healing pets? I do but not with pc's. This may also be a note to remember instead of waiting to the last min to heal a pet if its true. If pet is one of many tanks, i usually dont bother healing, but if he is primary/secondary, i try and keep an eye on pet or have mage tell me if pet needs a heal..its easier for mage to check as he can /report health. <BR>    Mainly tho, it will depend on group makeup and the mage really and whether i can spare the mana if i heal the pet.
