I've played a Magi to 49 and a Cleric to 50. If you asked me, "would I heal?" Ummmm,..No!<P>1. The Magi gets pet only heal spells..If he does not use them, then tuff luck!<BR>2. The Magi Should save more of his Mana to chain cast another pet if needed.<BR>3. The Magi needs an Enchanter more than a Healing for his pet.<P>If you got the mana to burn then what the heck, heal it. But those pets get there Hitpoint back pretty fast.<P>Any Cleric that tries to take on the role of checking on the Pets health is putting the lives of the Group Members at risk. Save your Mana for what works and try not to feel bad about it. Next time the Magi *****es about his pet dying. Tell him to summon a better pet next time. And when the mana permits you will buff the pet. But you can't spend your time over his pet. Just be blunt about it. Really now, what can he do about it? If they don't like it, then they can die alone and get no reses from you. And you can move on to a group with a better pet player, like the Necro.
