<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> Healing a pet is not the cleric's priority? Pets can deal out huge amounts of damage. You're forgetting to calculate that the sooner a mob dies, the less damage everyone in your party takes, and the less mana it costs you. That mage's pet probably dealt out nearly as much damage as the monks, and the cleric should have seen it as a very important member of the group.  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Ok. First, a pet do not nearly do as much damage as a monk, this statement is totally ridiculous. even a paladin outdamages a pet.<BR>(paladin being the weakest melee in offense)<P>1- Earth pet is a nuisance in any group fighting strong mobs (root resisted or root takes hold and mob hits the tank instead of attempting to run. <P>2- Fire pet has no meaning in a group.<P>3- Air pet has very little use, even in dungeons. the stun doesnt proc quite as much as it should. the invis does not make them usefull in a dungeon, since a good mage (one that does not ask for his pet to be healed by someone else, for example), knows where his pet is at any given time.<P>4- Water pet is making up for the weakness of the mage himself. the only usefull pet in group, unless you need that root to hold a room (and in that case, the mobs must be pretty tough - meaning, root wont hold). Has very fast health regen.<P>Overall, the water pet is the only one worth summoning in a group. and that pet, for your information, is still extremly weak compared to tank/melee classes(damage-wise). he has more hp that the group`s monk, true. but who cares. if theres a monk or warrior in the group, the pet wont get hit. <P>And thats a good thing, because the monk has the highest defensive skills except the warrior. besides, the water pet gets backstab at 52. if they tank, they are being useless - a fire pet would do better.<P>Also. Renew Summoning = Pet Healing Spell(200HP). And, its very much easier for the mage to know his pet`s health ("i have 100% hit points left"), and to target and heal him. At high levels, though, its useless, of course...but so are the pets (almost). And its not like Mages have any problem with the spell slots - they have plenty of room there.<P>In every way that you could look at it, pets are by far inferior to any tank/melee class. they are usefull. but far from being worthy of a heal from someone else than his own (dumb oom) master. if the mage is oom, the cleric is oom too, obviously. As for buffs, Mages have the Burnout serie of pet-only buffs.<P>And thats without considering the fact that a *lot* of players are twinked/highly twinked, and will be even more as time passes. pet are not twinks, and will never be.<P><BR>I have much more to say about it, but this alone should do as proof that pets are the master`s concern, not the healer`s (whom a whole group depends on). <P>Anyway. im not saying Mages arent good, not at all. They can be highly sought after, especially for long raids. i love to have a mage in my groups, but that has nothing to do with their pets.<P>There are many thing a cleric can do when FM in a fully healed party (not including pet, which is not a party member). I dont want to be mean, trust me..but..if you end up healing the pet(s), you need some new ideas :/   <P><BR>oh well, i guess you play just fine if you reached your current level, whatever it may be, unless you have a guild PLing your ignorant a*s    <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"> . Just a thought    <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> <P>Have fun playing EQ..because its almost over! at last    <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0"> . Well unless you get screwed and end up buying SoL, which is going to be, the way it looks, another  shamefull expansion just like Diablo2`s or Baldur`s Gate 2`s.    <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0">     <IMG SRC="redface.gif" border="0">    <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0">    <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0">  <BR>..oh well, i know im not the only one who realized this at least. <BR>   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
