<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I also play a magician as well as a cleric, for whatever that's worth.<P>I can't believe some of the people who say that a cleric who doesn't take care of the pets are not doing their job.  A cleric's job is to ensure that the party survives... period.  If all of the PC's are alive at the end of the fight, then the cleric has done his job.  <P>That being said, you have to understand a little of where the magicians come from.  While any pets are a significant enhancement to the party, they are more than that to the magician.  Wrapped up in the pet is the only form of crowd control that a magician will ever have in the game.  Without a pet, and with a MOB on them, a magician is in serious straights, since all of their pet summoning spells are fairly long cast time.  In fact, most of their DD's are longer than the recycle time for usually 2-3 MOB swings.  Combined with low armor class, only luck will allow them to get their spells off.
</FONT>
