<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Anthe"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00010956"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/priv_message.gif" BORDER='0' ALT="Send New Private Message"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=10&t=000528&reply_num=000032&u=00010956"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=10&t=000528&replyto=000032"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Clerics that refuse to heal pets are foolish, ignorant clerics.<P>Pets out damage practically every other melee class besides a rogue.  Keeping a good pet alive is good for the group.  After around level 45, when warriors start going for super fast, low damage weapons - a pet can totally humiliate a warrior, Sk, Pal, Ranger and sometimes monks in dmg output.  Keep in mind warriors aren't supposed to kill stuff...they just keep the mob's attention while others kill it.<P>Pets are casters' best DOT.  If you force them to resummon a pet, you are risking getting a weaker pet while costing the caster a lot of mana to summon, haste and buff the pet....mana they normally expend during normal fighting.  By not healing their pet, you just with-held the offensive magic of your caster for 2-4 fights, effectively costing you MORE mana in the long run by having the fights last longer.<P>Pets also generally have around the same, or more HPs than like-level warriors depending on the pet type.  This means that when your lvl 56 mage pal asks you to heal his earth pet that's sitting at 6% health, he's down 3khps or more.  It's not like your heal will be wasted.<P>In the original posters case, where he was too OOM to heal the pet...sure let it die v/s one of the party members.  But, if you got your ugly stick out beating on a mob instead of medding and this happens, or if you are playing weak and decrepid wizard with puny nukes instead of medding, you should get replaced.<P>Pets have a bad rap because of pathing bugs and the sometimes difficulty in controlling them in multiple pulls - as such the general populas tends to think pets as below-par for most situations.  This is so out of warp it's silly.  <P>Lastly, regarding the special casters heal for their pets - after around level 35 it becomes useless for practical reasons.  At level 20 there is a heal costing 100mana that heals 200hp.  At level 20, this is a nice heal.  At level 34, it becomes iffy as to it's beneficial purpose.  After lvl 39, when pets really start getting HPs, it's an excersize in futility.  By the time you hit 49, the spell is on page 40 in your spellbook.  Example:  Next time your level 50 warrior with 3400hps is down to 10% life, see how enjoyable it is to heal him using greater heal.  Now, imagine it healing 80hp less per cast, and with a 4 second recast timer.  In combat.  Using the equivilent skill of magic as evocation for clerics.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
