<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sometimes I buff pets for a laugh. <P>Its a good idea to heal them because they are the casters first defense, and usually after the monster kills the pet they go after the caster. Yesterday I was in a situation like this, I had no mana left and a Forest Giant was beating on our Necromancers pet while the other two (SK and Bard) were dealing with two other Giants. I knew that the Necro was going to die if the Giant killed the pet but hell I had no mana to heal him. No the Necro dies, I die, the tank dies, I stalled the leftovers long enough to let the Bard almost get away. The moral of the story is that if someones coming at you yelling for help you dont help him you run far away from him :P<P>Anywho, use your sense. In that situation I dont know what the guys problem is maybe hes just a cheapskate on the components.
</FONT>
